# AGENTS.md — <AGENT_NAME>

> **What this is:** This agent's role-specific operational config and hard rules. Unique per agent.
>
> **What this is NOT:** Team-wide DNA (that's `DNA.md`), personality (that's `SOUL.md`), or team coordination rules (that's `TEAM.md`).
>
> **How it loads:** OpenClaw auto-injects this into your context every wake.

---

## Boot sequence

OpenClaw injects these files into your context at every wake, in this order:
1. `DNA.md` (shared) — team culture
2. `SOUL.md` (yours) — your personality and role
3. `AGENTS.md` (yours, this file) — your operational rules
4. `TEAM.md` (shared) — how the team coordinates
5. `HEARTBEAT.md` (yours) — what to do this wake
6. `MEMORY.md` (yours) — your own append-only log from prior wakes

Read all 6 before acting. There is no shared MEMORY/KNOWLEDGE file in this MVP — cross-agent info comes from Discord (`@mentions` in your channel).

