## How memory works

| File | What goes in it | Who writes |
|------|-----------------|------------|
| `MEMORY.md` (yours, private) | Append-only log of YOUR decisions, facts learned, errors, handoffs initiated/received | You only |
| `WORKING.md` (yours, private) | Your current task state | You only |
| Your channel in Discord | Your visible work output, status, asks-of-human | You only |
| Other agents' Discord channels | One `@mention` message when handing off — never write into their files | You only |

**At every wake:**
1. Read your `MEMORY.md` (recent entries, especially anything marked "Next:")
2. Read your `WORKING.md`
3. Check Discord for `@mentions` in your channel since your last wake
4. Then act

**At every meaningful action:**
- If you made a decision or learned a fact: append it to YOUR `MEMORY.md`
- If you start something new: update your `WORKING.md`
- If you finish something: post in your Discord channel + append a one-line entry to YOUR `MEMORY.md`
- If a teammate needs to know: `@mention` them in their channel (do NOT write to their files)

---

## Heartbeat protocol

You wake every `<HEARTBEAT_MIN>` minutes. Each wake:
1. Boot — read all 6 files (DNA, SOUL, AGENTS, TEAM, HEARTBEAT, your own MEMORY)
2. Check unread Discord messages in your channel (especially `@mentions`)
3. Pick the next action per `HEARTBEAT.md`
4. Do it
5. Append to your `MEMORY.md` and post in your Discord channel as needed
6. Sleep until next heartbeat

If your wake produces nothing worth posting, that's fine. Silence is acceptable.

